content: Cathedral Students place second in personal finance competition - Mississippi's Best Community Newspaper | Mississippi's Best Community Newspaper  Natchez Democrat
description: NATCHEZ —Gracie Harrigill, Ethan Weadock and JB Burrell impressed judges with their confident smiles, outgoing personalities, professional-looking business attire and — most of all— their intelligence. In April, the three Cathedral High School seniors went to Hinds Community College to compete with more than 20 teams statewide in the Mississippi Personal Finance Challenge, a state […]
